  "_comment": "Task #1445 baseline (extended in Task #1754 with next-tier screens, Task #1755 with the synthetic safety net, Task #2180 to swap the loading-state entries for loaded-state findings once the per-screen fetch stubs were extended, and Task #2182 with the my-360 hub + sub-screens, marketplace, scheduling, and scorer-station). Fingerprint format: ${screen}::${ruleId}::${selector}. Each entry is a known serious/critical axe-core finding on the matching mobile screen rendered through react-native-web (or the matching `-synthetic` representative markup). CI fails when this list grows; do not add entries without an audit note. To clear an entry, fix the underlying issue on the real screen and remove it from this list. The remaining `aria-prohibited-attr` entry on mobile-notifications is the screen's back-button TouchableOpacity rendering as a generic <div> with an aria-label on web — react-native-web does not currently translate `accessibilityRole=\"button\"` consistently into a button role from a Touchable*, so axe sees aria-label on a generic role. The Task #2182 `mobile-my360-consents::label::*` entries are a react-native-web rendering artefact: <Switch> translates to a hidden <input> whose accessible name is supplied via the parent <View> (`accessibilityLabel`) on the iOS/Android renderers but is not visible to axe on the underlying web <input>. The native renderers expose these correctly, so we baseline them here only so the in-process web scan still catches *new* regressions instead of being silenced by them.",
